<bibRefCitation id="5D4A5CB0FFC5FFB5FD19FE8AFCABFEC1" author="Eppelsheim, E." box="[657,867,303,330]" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" pagination="419 - 430" refId="ref4195" refString="Eppelsheim, E. Neue Staphylinen von Amur // Deutsche entomologische Zeitschrift. - 1887. - 31. - P. 419 - 430." type="book chapter" year="1887">Eppelsheim, 1887</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). It can be reliably distinguished from these species by the shape of the male sternite VIII and by the shape of the aedeagus. For illustrations of the aedeagi of 
<taxonomicName id="FEDB5AC2FFC5FFB5FDB0FED5FD2DFE02" authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="2003" box="[568,741,367,394]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplicitatis">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC5FFB5FDB0FED5FD2DFE02" box="[568,741,367,394]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">G. simplicitatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="5D4A5CB0FFC5FFB5FC9EFED5FC6AFE01" author="Pace, R." box="[790,930,367,394]" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" pagination="621 - 660" refId="ref4270" refString="Pace, R. Gyrophaenini della Cina (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) // Revue Suisse de zoologie. - 2003. - 110. - P. 621 - 660." type="book chapter" year="2003">Pace (2003)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
